<p>The <b>American Civil War</b> was fought in the <a href="a/../United_States">United States</a> from <a href="a/../1861">1861</a> until <a href="a/../1865">1865</a> between the United States &ndash; forces coming mostly from the 23 <a href="a/../U.S._northern_states">northern states</a> of the <a href="a/../United_States">Union</a> &ndash; and the newly-formed <a href="a/../Confederate_States_of_America">Confederate States of America</a>, which consisted of 11 <a href="a/../U.S._southern_states">southern states</a> that had declared their <a href="a/../Secession">secession</a>. There were various names used to describe the war itself, its combatants, armies, and battles (see the article <a href="a/../Naming_the_American_Civil_War">Naming the American Civil War</a>).
</p>
<table border="0" id="toc"><tr id="toctitle"><td align="center">
<b>Contents</b> <script type="text/javascript">showTocToggle("show","hide")</script></td></tr><tr id="tocinside"><td>
